12/06/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Speaking after a two-hour meeting Wednesday (11 June) with Prime Minister Branko Crvenkovski, Democratic Union of Integration leader Ali Ahmeti said Macedonia faces no danger of destabilisation. He added that local authorities, in co-operation with police and international peacekeepers, are constantly monitoring security on the ground to avoid an escalation of violence.
Also Wednesday, parliament adopted the National Strategy on Defence and Security. It outlines guidelines for improving the security and was drafted in accordance with the Ohrid framework agreement. The opposition VMRO-DPMNE and Liberal Party remain critical on the strategy. (MIA, A1 TV, Makfax - 11/06/03)
